{
  "stem": "14060.8",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To the best of my knowledge, nobody survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Apparently a lot of them got shot in-- in-- in-- in the forest outside and eventually some were taken on a march.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I have not met or heard anybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if there are, I don't know where they are.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The other interesting Buchenwald camp story is that as it was a very old established concentration camp, the oldest in Germany, all the important Socialists and Communists were sent there, some to Dachau as well, but this was the first one.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And eventually, like in all places, like in a prison, the senior prisoners become somehow the bosses or organizers what really happens in the camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "OK, the instructions and the orders came from the SS and the Germans, but what went on in detail in the camp was up to them, which could mean life or death at the time.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And what has happened, the-- the-- the Germans, out of maybe gratefulness or whatever, when they liquidated the Auschwitz camp, they-- they killed a lot of people and gassed them, but the remaining people who are kapos and blockaltestes and criminals who did all the worst things, they created a transport-- they made up a transport, and they sent them to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It became common knowledge in February of '45, when we were there, that these people arrived from Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We knew it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, people recognized people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was put to the Socialist/Communist management there that these people killed people, and these people maimed people to the point that they had no chance of survival.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was a guy by-- a very tall man, a German, gentile.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "His name was Gustave.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was a Communist.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He became, I think, quite a big mucker in East Germany afterwards.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He survived.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
